data.content:
Here's how to make your page theme-aware:

## XAML ŌĆö `AppThemeBinding`

Replace every hardcoded color with `AppThemeBinding`, providing a `Light` and `Dark` value:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             BackgroundColor="{AppThemeBinding Light=White, Dark=#1E1E1E}">

    <VerticalStackLayout Padding="20" Spacing="15">

        <Label Text="Welcome!"
               FontSize="24"
               TextColor="{AppThemeBinding Light=#333333, Dark=#F0F0F0}" />

        <Label Text="This page follows your system theme."
               TextColor="{AppThemeBinding Light=#666666, Dark=#CCCCCC}" />

        <Button Text="Get Started"
                BackgroundColor="{AppThemeBinding Light=#2196F3, Dark=#BB86FC}"
                TextColor="{AppThemeBinding Light=White, Dark=Black}" />

    </VerticalStackLayout>
</ContentPage>
```

That's it ŌĆö the OS theme is detected automatically. No event wiring needed.

## C# equivalent

Use `SetAppThemeColor` (for colors) or `SetAppTheme<T>` (for any property):

```csharp
var page = new ContentPage();
page.SetAppThemeColor(ContentPage.BackgroundColorProperty, Colors.White, Color.FromArgb("#1E1E1E"));

var title = new Label { Text = "Welcome!", FontSize = 24 };
title.SetAppThemeColor(Label.TextColorProperty, Color.FromArgb("#333333"), Color.FromArgb("#F0F0F0"));

var button = new Button { Text = "Get Started" };
button.SetAppThemeColor(Button.BackgroundColorProperty, Color.FromArgb("#2196F3"), Color.FromArgb("#BB86FC"));
button.SetAppThemeColor(Button.TextColorProperty, Colors.White, Colors.Black);
```

## Key things to know

1. **Android requirement** ŌĆö your `MainActivity` must include `ConfigChanges.UiMode` or theme changes cause a full activity restart instead of a smooth switch.

2. **More than two themes?** Use `ResourceDictionary` swapping with `DynamicResource` bindings instead ŌĆö `AppThemeBinding` only supports light and dark.

3. **Read/override the theme in code:**
   ```csharp
   // Read current OS theme
   AppTheme current = Application.Current.RequestedTheme;

   // Force dark mode
   Application.Current.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Dark;

   // Follow system again
   Application.Current.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Unspecified;
   ```
